## Example: |x−5| − |x−1| = 2

### The Number Line Setup

```
←————————•————————————•————————→
        x=1                x=5

  Case1  |    Case 2    |  Case 3
  x < 1  |  1 ≤ x < 5  |  x ≥ 5
```

---

## What Happens in Each Case

### Case 1: x < 1 (LEFT of both points)
```
←——[x]——•————————————•————————→
        x=1          x=5

|x-1| = -(x-1)  [x is LEFT of 1, so negative]
|x-5| = -(x-5)  [x is LEFT of 5, so negative]
```
Equation becomes:
-(x-5) - -(x-1) = 2
→ 4 = 2 ❌ **No solution**

---

### Case 2: 1 ≤ x < 5 (BETWEEN the points)
```
←————————•——————[x]——•————————→
        x=1          x=5

|x-1| = (x-1)   [x is RIGHT of 1, so positive]
|x-5| = -(x-5)  [x is LEFT of 5, so negative]
```
Equation becomes:
-(x-5) - (x-1) = 2
-x+5-x+1 = 2
-2x = -4 → **x = 2** ✅

```
←————————•——[x=2]————•————————→
        x=1          x=5
        
Distance to 1 = 1 unit
Distance to 5 = 3 units
Difference    = 2 ✓
```

---

### Case 3: x ≥ 5 (RIGHT of both points)
```
←————————•————————————•——[x]——→
        x=1          x=5

|x-1| = (x-1)  [x is RIGHT of 1, positive]
|x-5| = (x-5)  [x is RIGHT of 5, positive]
```
Equation becomes:
(x-5) - (x-1) = 2
→ -4 = 2 ❌ **No solution**

---

## Final Picture
```
←————————•——[★]———————•————————→
        x=1  x=2     x=5

★ = Solution!

From x=2:
|←1 unit→|←——3 units——→|
   to 1          to 5

3 - 1 = 2 ✓
```

---

## The Golden Rule 🔑

| Region | x−1 sign | x−5 sign |
|--------|----------|----------|
| x < 1 | − | − |
| 1≤x<5 | + | − |
| x ≥ 5 | + | + |

The sign **flips** every time you cross a critical point!

